The late Leonard Cohen&#8217;s famous track &#8220;Hallelujah&#8221; has entered the Billboard Hot 100 chart for the first time.The musician&#8217;s iconic song debuted at number 59 on the chart for the week ending November 17, Billboard reports. The move was due to a surge in sales and streaming figures following the star&#8217;s death on November 7, which was announced some days later on November 10. Cohen was 82 at the time of his passing.&#8220;Hallelujah&#8221; was first revealed in 1984, appearing on Cohen&#8217;s album &#8220;Various Positions.&#8221;-AFP